Basic element of language

This article concerns the elementary building block of any spoken or written communication—a word—whose very existence is apparently a source of endless debate among linguists who, unsurprisingly, have yet to agree on a definition that doesn’t involve a footnote the size of a novel. If you were actually looking for the piece of software that makes you sound like a corporate drone, there’s always [Microsoft Word](/Microsoft_Word). And if you’re after a disambiguation page that probably contains even more obscure references, you can wander over to [Word (disambiguation)](/Word_(disambiguation)).

